Ultimate leg-bearing segment
: metasternite wider than long, trapezoidal, length 0.06, maximum width 0.13 (length/width ratio 0.4); presternite elongated, 0.44 times as long as previous metasternite (
Fig. 9E
). Ultimate legs straight, length 0.47 (2.2 as long as penultimate leg); each coxopleuron with 4 coxal pores opening below to the metasternite; tarsus 1.6 times as long as tibia, with a well developed terminal spine (
Fig. 9E–F
